==English==
===Etymology===
Middle English ''herbage'', from Old French ''[[erbage]]'', from Medieval Latin ''[[herbagium]]'', from {{L.}} ''[[herba]]'', grass

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

#herbs collectively
#[[herbaceous]] [[plant]] growth, especially [[grass]].
#the fleshy, often edible, parts of plants.
#right of pasture.

